/* =========================================
   QUERY 1
   Customer Delivery Exception Report
   ========================================= */

-- Business purpose:
-- This report exposes delayed shipments with customer, geography, sales rep,
-- and order value in one result set. It is useful for operational follow-up
-- and is kept intentionally simple for Week 2 defense and review.

SELECT
    so.order_id,
    c.customer_code,
    (
        SELECT r.country_name
        FROM dim_regions AS r
        WHERE r.region_id = c.region_id
    ) AS country_name,
    sr.rep_name,
    (
        SELECT d.full_date
        FROM dim_date AS d
        WHERE d.date_id = so.order_date_id
    ) AS order_date,
    (
        SELECT d.full_date
        FROM dim_date AS d
        WHERE d.date_id = so.ship_date_id
    ) AS ship_date,
    DATEDIFF(
        DAY,
        (
            SELECT d.full_date
            FROM dim_date AS d
            WHERE d.date_id = so.order_date_id
        ),
        (
            SELECT d.full_date
            FROM dim_date AS d
            WHERE d.date_id = so.ship_date_id
        )
    ) AS shipping_delay_days,
    ot.order_net_value
FROM fact_sales_orders AS so
INNER JOIN dim_customers AS c
    ON so.customer_id = c.customer_id
INNER JOIN dim_sales_reps AS sr
    ON so.sales_rep_id = sr.sales_rep_id
INNER JOIN
(
    SELECT
        order_id,
        CAST(SUM(net_amount) AS DECIMAL(18,2)) AS order_net_value
    FROM fact_order_line_items
    GROUP BY
        order_id
) AS ot
    ON so.order_id = ot.order_id
WHERE so.ship_date_id IS NOT NULL
  AND so.order_status <> 'Cancelled'
  AND DATEDIFF(
        DAY,
        (
            SELECT d.full_date
            FROM dim_date AS d
            WHERE d.date_id = so.order_date_id
        ),
        (
            SELECT d.full_date
            FROM dim_date AS d
            WHERE d.date_id = so.ship_date_id
        )
    ) > 14
ORDER BY
    shipping_delay_days DESC,
    ot.order_net_value DESC,
    so.order_id;

Review:
This is a useful reporting query with a clear business purpose and a sensible final output. 
The delayed-shipment focus is easy to understand, and the derived order value subquery is a good way to aggregate line-item revenue at the order level before joining it into the report. 
The filtering logic is also aligned with the use case because it keeps only shipped, non-cancelled orders and highlights the most severe delays first.
The main area for improvement is performance and readability. The repeated scalar subqueries against dim_date and dim_regions work logically, but they make the query harder to maintain and can become less efficient as data grows. 
Replacing those scalar lookups with explicit JOINs would make the query easier to follow and more scalable. Overall, the query is correct and business-relevant, with a good foundation that would benefit from a more join-friendly structure.
